\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Usage:
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\
1. Choose 'System Preferences' from the Apple menu\
2. Select 'Screen Saver' (it's in the top right corner)\
3. Choose 'Flurry' from the list of available screensavers\
3. Click on 'Configure'\
4. Change settings to your own personal taste\
	
\f0\b OR
\f1\b0 \
    Select a preset from the popup menu\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b \cf0 Presets
\f1\b0 \
\
Presets store configurations of Flurries. You can create as many as you like, each with completely different sets of Flurries. Each preset can be assigned to a key, so when that key is pressed when the screensaver is active, that preset becomes the current one. To try it out, press keys 1 to 5 using the initial preset configurations. \
\

\f0\b Random preset selection
\f1\b0 \
\
If you enable the check box in the bottom of the configuration dialog, a random preset will be used each time your screensaver is run. \
\

\f0\b Multiple 'Flurries'
\f1\b0 \
\
