The table on the left of the configuration window allows you to have a 'Flurry displayed on none, some or all of your monitors. Select one or more Flurries and edit their attributes using the controls on the right of the window. You can even edit the name of the Flurry, so you can remember which ones you like. \
\
The first column shows the colour mode that the Flurry is using - the colour will change just like it does when Flurry is running. \
\
The second column displays the number of streams on this Flurry. \
\
The name of the Flurry can be edited and will be saved for you. \
\
The remaining columns will differ from one computer to another. There will be one column for each monitor connected to your computer. The check box indicates if that particular Flurry will be displayed on that particular monitor. If you do not wish to delete a Flurry, you can disable it by unchecking all of the monitors for that row. \
